 "Teachers should keep the following in mind when using this iDevice: <ol><li>Think about the number of different types of activity planned for your resource that will be visually signalled in the content. Avoid using too many different types or classification of activities otherwise learner may become confused. Usually three or four different types are more than adequate for a teaching resource.<\/li><li>From a visual design perspective, avoid having two iDevices immediately following each other without any text in between. If this is required, rather collapse two questions or events into one iDevice. <\/li><li>Think about activities where the perceived benefit of doing the activity outweighs the time and effort it will take to complete the activity. <\/li><\/ol>": "Ovo u\u010ditelji trebaju da imaju na umu kad koriste iUre\u0111aj: <ol><li> Razmislite o broju razli\u010ditih aktivnosti koje planirate za va\u0161 izvor informacija, koje \u0107e biti vizualno signalizirane usadr\u017eaju. Izbegavajte da koristite previ\u0161e razli\u010ditih tipova ili kasifikacija aktivnosti, jer u\u010denicimogu da se zbune. Obi\u010dno su tri do \u010detiri razli\u010dita tipa vi\u0161e nego dovoljni za edukativni izvor informacija.<\/li><li> Sa stanovi\u0161ta vizualnog dizajna, izbegavajte da imate dva iUre\u0111aja odmah jedan nakon drugog bez teksta izme\u0111u njih. Ako je to neophodno onda je bolje da dva pitanja ili doga\u0111aja stavite u jedan iUre\u0111aj. <\/li><li> Razmislite o aktivnosti u kojima opa\u017eena korist i u\u010dinak vr\u0161enja aktivnosti ima nadma\u0161uje vreme i napor da se zavr\u0161i aktivnost. <\/li><\/ol>", 
